column1: Table 4:  Summary data table for Ascore analysis of peptides found in this study
Chromatin, DNA-binding, DNA repair or DNA replication protein
Receptor, channel, transporter or cell surface protein

§ indicates sites known to be phosphorylated, though not necessarily by ATM/R.  Peptide Change indicates if the Ascore program modified the original peptide in any way to improve scores.  Original sequences are shown in the Sequence column, sequences used for scoring are shown in the Ascore Sequence column.  Ascore values correspond to the ordinal number of the phosphorylation site shown in the Ascore Sequence column (first, secon, third).  Peptides with more than three phosphorylation sites do not have Ascore values.  N/A indicates 100% certainty of proper phosphorylation site localization, as no other potential phosphorylation site is available.  Green indicates sites with Ascore values over the 95% confidence threshold, grey indicates Ascore values for non-motif sites.
